SUMMARY

In the 1930s, an elderly Tonto tells a young boy the
tale of John Reid, the Lone Ranger. An idealistic
lawyer, he rides with his brother and fellow Texas
Rangers in pursuit of the notorious Butch Cavendish.
Ambushed by the outlaw and left for dead, John Reid is
rescued by the renegade Comanche, Tonto, at the
insistence of a mysterious white horse and offers to
help him to bring Cavendish to justice. Becoming a
reluctant masked rider with a seemingly incomprehensible
partner, Reid pursues the criminal against all obstacles.
However, John and Tonto learn that Cavendish is only
part of a far greater injustice and the pair must fight
it in an adventure that would make them a legend.
